                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 863.50/37: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-23">December 23,
                            1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. [From Lansing.] Your number 96, December 21st, 10 p.m. I approve of the
                    proposed replies to French Embassy and Swiss <pb facs="0296" n="208"
                        xml:id="pg_208"/> Legation. Suggest that you advise American Legation,
                    Berne, if you have not already done so. Lansing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
